Seven people were injured – two of them seriously – on Tuesday when a bakkie overturned in the Bo-Kaap. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement a number of emergency services responded to the scene. According to Meiring, the bakkie was found lying on its roof in the road. The passengers who had been travelling on the back of the vehicle were scattered around at the scene of the incident. Two men sustained serious injuries, while five others had only moderate injuries. The patients were treated on the scene and transported to a nearby hospital for further treatment, Meiring said.    